LOOKING FOR A COMPOSER

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm looking for a **composer** for a 8 **-minute student short film** called *Space Baby*.

A **sci-fi Comedy / 80s-inspired film** about two college students who find a baby alien and end up raising it as their kid.

The film is already shot, and I‚Äôm looking for someone to create an **80s sci-fi themed score**, mainly for emotional and atmospheric moments. Think inspiration like **Back to the Future, Ghostbusters, and The Breakfast Club** (synthy, warm, nostalgic vibes).

This is a **paid opportunity**.

If you‚Äôre interested, please  email at wagnercarrera138@gmail. com me with samples of your work. Thanks!

Actors!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions. 

This is more than just filmmaking; it's a journey to elevate our craft and careers to new heights! Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free! 

Complete this form to join us. [https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7](https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExOWgxMkV1M0hERHZPcnRiZHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR5k9IvyEVLNR7KSIH-49als_mHzt2jmGaMVG-0US9AEEf0j7Noco2gsk8uinQ_aem_Bhp-OAZ6lp-AUQSLYq-m5Q)

We‚Äôre putting together a documentary-style filmed project exploring how people experience and overcome phobias.

We‚Äôre looking for people from all walks of life who would be open to taking part on camera.

It could be a fear of dogs that stops you going out, a fear of flying if you need to travel for something important, a fear of public speaking with an upcoming speech, or an unusual or less talked-about phobia you‚Äôve lived with for a long time.

Many people feel embarrassed about their fear or try to hide it. This project aims to explore those experiences in a respectful, non-sensational way, focusing on the process rather than shock value.

**Dates to be confirmed. The position is unpaid, with reasonable expenses covered, and participants will receive free phobia treatment as part of the project.**

Filming will take place over a number of months, with times and dates arranged individually with each participant.

Filming would be discussed fully in advance, and participation is entirely voluntary.

If this sounds like you, feel free to **DM me** for more information, or comment below and I‚Äôll reply.

Hey-Yah All ! Ein gesundes neues Jahr an alle.

Wir haben schon in einigen Filmen mitgespielt, auch in Serien.

items.text:
## üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äî JERRY

**Project:** Lie Detector (Short Film)
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Dates:**  Sundays Jan 25 or Sunday Feb 01
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project (Reel‚Äëworthy material)

**Actors looking to play a layered character outside their comfort zone are strongly encouraged to apply.**

ROLE: JERRY

**Age Range:** 30‚Äì45
**Ethnicity:** Caucasian

**Gender:** Male
CHARACTER SNAPSHOT

Jerry is Amber‚Äôs husband ‚Äî thoughtful, intelligent, and quietly dependable. He‚Äôs the kind of man people trust instinctively. Soft‚Äëspoken. Observant. Safe. Which is exactly why he‚Äôs unpredictable.

Jerry isn‚Äôt loud, cruel, or obviously broken. His betrayal doesn‚Äôt come from malice, but from emotional absence ‚Äî a man who learned to disappear while standing right next to someone. When the truth surfaces, it‚Äôs not explosive. It‚Äôs devastating in its calm.

This role lives in restraint. What Jerry *doesn‚Äôt* say matters more than what he does.

PERFORMANCE NOTES
* Subtle, internal performance
* Strong control of silence, pauses, and micro‚Äëexpressions
* Chemistry with Amber is critical ‚Äî intimacy without sentimentality
* We‚Äôre looking for an actor who can make the audience *want to believe him*

This is **not** a villain role. It‚Äôs a human one.

WHY THIS ROLE MATTERS

Jerry sits at the emotional fault line of the story.

His choices force Amber to confront the limits of technology, trust, and perception.

Handled well, this role will linger with the audience long after the film ends.

Please apply at soultales.ca@gmail.com

**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( ≈ölƒÖsk )**

** **

**Temat 2 ‚Äì ‚Äò‚ÄôWampirzyca w baroku 1700‚Äô‚Äô**

Postaƒá kobiety ubrana najpierw w suknie czarnƒÖ oraz peleryne z kapturem. Do tego czarna d≈Çuga peruka oraz czarne paznokcie. W kolejnym etapie sesji motyw sensualny.

** **

**Temat 3 ‚Äì ‚Äò‚ÄôDuchy lasu‚Äô‚Äô**

** **

**Temat 4 ‚Äì ‚Äò‚ÄôKleopatra‚Äô‚Äô**

Postaƒá kobiety ubrana w str√≥j piracki: kamizelka, koszula, kapelusz, spodnie i kapelusz a do tego rekwizyty pistolet czy kufel piwa.

 

**Temat 6 ‚Äì ‚Äò‚ÄôLara Croft ‚Äò‚Äô**

Postaƒá kobiety wzorowanej z tytu≈Çowej gry Tomb Rider.

 

** **

**Zapraszam na stronƒô**

sharedPost.text:
The Currency Of Civilization Is Art.
¬†
‚ÄúActing wasn‚Äôt born today.¬† It‚Äôs a tradition of 2,000 years. A civilization isn‚Äôt defined by how much money somebody made or how many BMWs people have in their garages.¬† If you visit the Metropolitan Museum of Art, you won‚Äôt see exhibits of people‚Äôs bank accounts.¬† The currency of civilization is Art.‚Äù
¬†
‚ÄúYou have the possibility of carrying these riches of two millennia inside you.¬† But you
cannot transmit what you have not received.¬† So you must study acting the way a priest or a rabbi studies scripture. You have the privilege of forging our link from that history to the future.‚Äù

Stella Adler 

Come train with respected ctor and coach, Michael Caruana. Expert guidance and coaching, trusted, since 1996, at bongo productions. 

Talent Manager Norbert Abrams say‚Äôs about Michael Caruana‚Ä¶

‚ÄúWhen I joined Noble Talent & Modelling 2.5 decades ago, Michael Caruana was a popular acting coach whose name was frequently recommended by other Agents and professional actors alike. Michael has a keen eye for talent and works caringly to maximize the efforts of each actor. He motivates with a quiet passion, elevating the actors‚Äô character and spirit to be inspired to achieve their personal best.
¬†
Michael‚Äôs referrals have ignited many burgeoning careers on my roster over the years. He is trusted, respected and lauded as a coach and educator in my world. When I meet with Michael‚Äôs students, they reflect his thoughtful, disciplined and enlightened approach to their training. Michael provides his students a safe environment where they are free to take guarded risks to grow as artists.
¬†
When I receive a referral email with Michael Caruana at bongo productions in the subject line, I open it with a sense of urgency.‚Äù
¬†
Norbert Abrams
Noble Caplan Abrams Talent Management

Private Coaching.
Scene-study.
Audition Technique

Comprehensive training with our Certificate Program.

Professional coaching, with Michael Caruana, at bongo productions, trusted, since 1996! www.bongoproductions.com

If you‚Äôre doing a live callback online, always prep first.
Remember, first impressions count.

Before you go live do some prep !

1.Check the space and background you‚Äôre in to make sure it is clean, neutral, and distraction free

2.Test the lighting so your face is clearly lit

3.Test the sound to ensure it is clear with no echo or background noise

4.Check your internet connection

A few minutes of prep can be the difference between a smooth, confident callback and avoidable stress.

#marksummerscasting #marksummers #castingdirector #callbacks

* **CUBANS**
* **MONGOLIANS**
* **BULGARIANS**
* **HULGARIANS**

üé• Looking for Confident On-Camera Talent for Public Interaction TikTok Videos 

I‚Äôm looking for a confident, charismatic on-camera personality for a series of short-form, public-interaction videos for a wellness brand.

This role is heavily improv-based. You‚Äôll be approaching people in public and engaging in real, unscripted conversations on camera. The ability to think on your feet, read people quickly, and go back-and-forth naturally is essential.

This is not scripted acting. The content is playful, high-energy, conversational, and humor-driven ‚Äî not aggressive or mean-spirited.

You do not need to film or edit anything. I will handle all production. You just need to be comfortable on camera and talking to strangers.

$20/hour 

Please send any similar content you‚Äôve done or even your Instagram/tiktok link helps.

topComments.text:
Hello! 

I would be perfect for this.

I‚Äôm a naturally charismatic and outgoing person who thrives on connecting with others. I‚Äôve dabbled in comedy and commercial acting, which has given me strong improv skills and the confidence to think on my feet in unscripted situations. I‚Äôm also very comfortable on camera, having performed regularly as a singer on my church‚Äôs worship team, which has taught me how to engage an audience and be authentic in front of people.

I genuinely enjoy playful, high-energy interactions and have a knack for reading people quickly and responding naturally ‚Äî exactly what‚Äôs needed for spontaneous public engagement content. I‚Äôm confident I can bring fun, relatable energy to your TikTok videos while making people feel at ease on camera.

I‚Äôm interested, but have no context.

When? Where? For how long? 

What will I be asked to talk about or react? 

I‚Äôm a great improviser, but won‚Äôt step in front of a camera without more security/context.

üé≠üåüURGENT CASTING CALL! üé≠üåü

We still need to cast a couple of minor roles for the upcoming  **‚ÄúA View From the Bridge‚Äù by Arthur Miller. **

**Immigration Officer #1/ Crowd  - **

**(male supporting, Playing age 35-55)**

An Immigration OÔ¨Écer who comes late in the play to arrest Marco and Rodolpho, after Eddie

has called the Immigration Bureau.

A Neighbour from the community in the final crowd scene

**Mr Lipari the Butcher  - **

**(male, ensemble, no lines, Playing age 40-60)**

An Italian American butcher who lives in Eddie‚Äôs building. He has two family members who are

illegal immigrants, staying in his apartment. They are discovered by immigration oÔ¨Écers when

they go to arrest Marco and Rodolpho, who are staying with him after being turned out by Eddie.

A Neighbour from the community in the final crowd scene

Please contact the Director - Jo Emery on **joemery@me.com **

**Performance Dates for show: **Wednesday 8th to Saturday 11th April 2026

Evenings at 7.45pm, Saturday matin√©e at 2.30pm

**Rehearsals begin: **These will take place on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 7.45pm from mid January 2026 at Watford Pump House Theatre. 

Pump House Theatre, Local Board Road, Watford, WD17 2JP

A modern staging of Arthur Miller‚Äôs timeless classic about deep-rooted and dangerously illicit desire.  In Brooklyn, Longshoreman Eddie Carbone welcomes his wife Beatrice‚Äôs Sicilian immigrant cousins to the land of the free. But when one of them falls for Catherine, the beautiful niece that he and Beatrice have brought up as their own daughter, they discover that freedom comes at a price. Eddie‚Äôs jealous mistrust exposes a deep, unspeakable secret ‚Äì one that drives him to commit the ultimate betrayal not only of his family but also the close-knit community in which they live, with devastating consequences.

Based on an apparently true story, told to Miller by a lawyer who worked with longshoremen, ‚ÄúA View from the Bridge‚Äù was first performed in 1956, when the United States was entering a period of great prosperity after the hardships of WW2. Immigrants were arriving in their droves from war- torn Europe in search of a new life, where hope, hard work and ambition could give them the longed-for American Dream. This production will give the play a modern twist with contemporary cultural references. 

Tickets here - [www.pumphousetheatrecompany.com](http://www.pumphousetheatrecompany.com)

A modern staging of Arthur Miller‚Äôs timeless classic about deep-rooted and dangerously illicit desire.  In Brooklyn, Longshoreman Eddie Carbone welcomes his wife Beatrice‚Äôs Sicilian immigrant cousins to the land of the free. But when one of them falls for Catherine, the beautiful niece that he and Beatrice have brought up as their own daughter, they discover that freedom comes at a price. Eddie‚Äôs jealous mistrust exposes a deep, unspeakable secret ‚Äì one that drives him to commit the ultimate betrayal not only of his family but also the close-knit community in which they live, with devastating consequences.

Based on an apparently true story, told to Miller by a lawyer who worked with longshoremen, ‚ÄúA View from the Bridge‚Äù was first performed in 1956, when the United States was entering a period of great prosperity after the hardships of WW2. Immigrants were arriving in their droves from war- torn Europe in search of a new life, where hope, hard work and ambition could give them the longed-for American Dream. This production will give the play a modern twist with contemporary cultural references. 

Tickets here - [www.pumphousetheatrecompany.com](http://www.pumphousetheatrecompany.com)

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì HORROR feature film üé¨
Hey everyone,
I‚Äôm currently looking for actors for an independent horror project titled:
FLYING TO MADNESS
This is a psychological horror film inspired by travel vlogs, haunted locations, and reality-bending horror. With a lot of twists
üëª ABOUT THE PROJECT
3 sisters travel to Ibiza for a girls holiday.
After taking drugs and exploring a remote location, they become trapped in a looping nightmare involving a haunted house that won‚Äôt let them leave.
Think:
Psychological horror
Creeping dread rather than cheap jump scares
This is a low-budget indie project, made for experience, showreels, and festival submissions.
üé≠ ROLES AVAILABLE

ACTRESS 1
Female, early‚Äìmid 20s
Slim built or curvy 
Confident, outgoing, ‚Äúleader‚Äù type
Comfortable acting on camera and improvising dialogue
Lots of screen time available 

ACTRESS 2
Female, early‚Äìmid 20s
Slim built or curvy
More cautious / sarcastic personality
Strong reactions and emotional range
Lots of screen time available 

ACTRESS 3 
Female early - mid 20s
Slim built
Shy/Inclosed soft voice
Good with emotional expressions
Lots of screen time available 

ACTOR 4
Male, any age 20s‚Äì40s about 6 foot plus. 
Slim built
Mysterious, unsettling presence
Minimal dialogue but strong physical acting
Horror-focused role
No previous acting experience required ‚Äî just commitment and reliability.

üìç LOCATION
Filming location: (UK-based project)
Scotland four days in September 
Southend beach for one hour any time available 
Hotel scenes is for half a day but can do during scotland trip
London basement for two hours in October 
Nightclub scene for two hours in April the 22nd at 6pm as location I‚Äôd already booked
And an hour at a studio for greenscreen Footage. Anytime available 
Passport might be needed for actor 1 and 2 as we need a scene on a plane or might be able to edit in with greenscreen effect
Mostly interior scenes
Small cast, long shoot schedule
üí∞ PAYMENT
No payment at the time of filming but
10% rotary payments after the film sells. In the cinemas and app stores. Small indi project
but travel expenses covered as can be picked up by the director from your location you want. And taking to the filming location. And Brought home after the scenes
If your making your own way to the scenes we can‚Äôt cover travelling 
Food provided on shoot days
Full credit given
Will help to spice up your portfolio and get more experience as main actors in the film.
üì© HOW TO APPLY
If interested, please message our private company WhatsApp on 07492853834 
Or if you want you can email on mpl.87@outlook.com 

with:
Your name
Age
Any acting experience (if any)
A recent photo or selfie
Availability
also send a short intro video.
If you love horror, indie films, or want experience working on a creative project, I‚Äôd love to hear from you.
Thanks!
‚Äî Matt Littlechild 
Writer / Director ‚Äì Flying to Madness

topComments.text: Do you really believe your ultra low budget film will have cinema distribution?

This is an abysmal casting call. A feature length unpaid is already a bad start. But you won't even cover expenses if they need to travel unless you can directly pick them up? I'd be shocked if more than 15 people submit to this.

There's no incentive to do it. The idea is generic - so from an artistic viewpoint, there's not much to gain. There's no pay, which is understandable at the indie level - but I've never seen somebody not offer to pay transport. Ever in my life.

And why would you book filming dates before you cast? Why do people keep doing this?

I'm not being harsh. I've just ran a very successful casting campaign for my fourth short film. This is awful. I don't see why any actor would take it other than very low calibre, bad actors who are desperate..

Paying transport and food is a minimum.

*DIGITAL ART OPEN-CALL OPPORTUNITY IN NYC*

Start the new year by exhibiting your work **on Madison Ave** in NYC. This one-night digital art show at a five-level speakeasy art studio inside Herbwell, seeks artworks exploring **rebirth, evolution, endings, beginnings, and transformation**. Showcase your art in the same neighborhood as monumental museums and galleries like the MoMa.

All digital mediums welcome: Digital Paintings & Illustration, 3D Modeling & Digital Sculpture, Digital Collage & Vector Art, Digital Photography, Pixel Art, GIF Art / Animation, Glitch Art, Generative Art, Augmented Reality (AR) Art, Virtual Reality (VR) Art, AI Art, Mixed Media (with digital components), Video Art & Motion Graphics, NFTs & Blockchain-Backed Works, Interactive & Installation-Based Digital Works, Derivative works (where you hold rights to exhibit), Scanned Physical Works

**Why submit?**

‚Ä¢ Showcase your work in one of NYC‚Äôs most prestigious art corridors
‚Ä¢ Photos, documentation, and press coverage included
‚Ä¢ Connect with curators, collectors, and international artists
‚Ä¢ Feature in a multi-disciplinary event blending digital art, traditional art, and live music

If your work speaks to stepping into something new ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to see it.

**Apply here:** [https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC](https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC)

**CASTING CALL:**

Bellingham, WA. based independent producer / director is looking for talent for a micro budget, non union, short film.

**PROJECT DESCRIPTION:** Comedy short about an office interview with unexpected consequences.

**PRODUCER:** Jerome Wallerstein

**FILMING DATES**: March or April 2026

**FILMING LOCATION: **Deming, WA

**FILMING DURATION:** 1-2 days.

**UNION STATUS: **non-SAG-AFTRA

**USAGE:** Web, Social, in perpetuity, non-exclusive; submission to film festivals intended

**SUBMISSION DEADLINE:** February 5th, 2026

**TO APPLY: Please send headshot / photos, link to your reel or video snippets, to**

**[wallerstein@sbcglobal.net](mailto:wallerstein@sbcglobal.net)**

**with the title "Just A Few Questions" in the subject line.**

**SYNOPSIS: **During an initial job interview, a potential candidate is obsessively fixated on a subject that the staid and conservative management team is wholly unprepared to address.

**ROLES:**

**Gender specific Male roles:**1) Youngish-looking male who can pass for early to mid 20‚Äôs; well spoken, quick, but gives the vibe of involvement with vaguely illicit activities, 2) Two males who can pass for their late late 30‚Äôs ‚Äì late 40‚Äôs, somewhat conservative and staid, but hoping to disaffirm that impression. All roles require comedic timing and pacing and ability to play off each other.

**Rate: NON-PAID, compensation for travel available. Meals provided.**

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

We'll be casting shortly for a short film to shoot in the Northwich/Manchester area.
Plot is a heavy handed debt collector who gets the tables turned on him by a customer who owes money.

Computer nerd friend digs out dirt on debt collector helping the police bring him down.

This is a collective project where we will also be looking for Camera, sound, lighting and director. Equipment is available for the shoot.

items.text:
AUDITIONS OPEN: Collection of Short Plays in March in London

Happy New Year! We‚Äôre Broadmai Productions, and we‚Äôre excited to announce that auditions are now open for our upcoming performance, HAYWIRE: The Dark Side of New Technology. The performances will be held at The Drayton Arms on 22nd & 23rd March 2026, starting at 7:30 PM each night. (Cast required all day on 22nd March for get-in and from 18:00 each night). 

Auditions will be online and open tomorrow, 13th January, and continue until 24th January. All ages, genders and levels of experience welcome. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning, please email us at: contact@broadmai-productions.co.uk

Please express interest by 23rd January.

Once you reach out, we‚Äôll send you the scripts for the four short plays: PostMax6000, Wonderful, Beyond the Grave, and Simon. 

_______

AUDITION DETAILS:

 ‚Ä¢ Auditions are 20-minute slots. You will be asked to audition with 2-3 pages of your choice from the provided scripts.

 ‚Ä¢ Ideally, be off book, but it‚Äôs fine if not. 

 ‚Ä¢ The characters are flexible in terms of gender and age, except those for Beyond the Grave, which requires two male actors who resemble father and son.

_______

PLAY DESCRIPTIONS:

 ‚Ä¢ PostMax 6000: The PostMax 6000 is invented! A vast underground postal system capable of delivering

hundreds of letters across the country per second! But what‚Äôs this?! It‚Äôs just sucked Kinkelbert George inside! Will he be delivered to freedom? Or lost in postal purgatory?

 ‚Ä¢ Wonderful: Ben signs up for a research programme for a new-age medical device. It can detect hereditary

illness and diseases that he could develop‚Ä¶but it also lets him know, and hear, exactly how his

ancestors died. As detections become increasingly intense, Ben learns that knowledge about death is better left untold ‚Äî especially when it comes to children.

 ‚Ä¢ Beyond the Grave: A mysterious phone is delivered. When it rings, Reece answers it and finds his deceased father on the other end. Overwhelmed to hear his voice again and to learn that there is a way to bring him back to life, Reece starts to wonder if the rules of death are better left unbroken‚Ä¶

 ‚Ä¢ Simon: Simon has an all-inclusive getaway booked and paid for by his work. The location is perfect, the

hotel is perfect, Simon is perfect. And so is Simon ‚Äî the other Simon. And the other Simon. Wait, how many Simons are there?! Who‚Äôs the real Simon?!

_______

REHEARSALS: 

 ‚Ä¢ Rehearsals will be in-person in London, with a commitment of 1-2 sessions per week until the performances.

_______

COMPENSATION:

 ‚Ä¢ This will be a profit-share arrangement, with profits distributed after expenses are covered.

# üé•** CASTING CALL ‚Äì Actor/Actress for a Training Video**

At Panda Motion, we are looking for an **actor or actress** to play the role of a host/narrator in an approx. 25-minute cybersecurity training video series.

**Details:**

üé¨ **Project:** Corporate training video (6-7 episodes, approx. 4 minutes each, 25 mins total) for an LMS platform

ACTORS NEEDED!!! - Casting Call

We're casting 6 actors for a 15-minute student graduation short film, titled 'March On'.

Only apply if from England 

The Shooting will take place in mid-March.

William (27-33) - Veteran struggling with internal war trauma

Sarah (27-33) - William‚Äôs partner is navigating intense family pressure

Pete (29-36) - Confrontational brother who lacks situational empathy

Mary (50-65) - Overbearing, intoxicated mother demanding centre stage

Lisa (29-36) - Pete‚Äôs partner is observant of William‚Äôs distress

Thomas (28 - 35) - Fragile veteran bonding through shared pain

This is a student graduate film for the University of Portsmouth!

Transport and Food will be provided.

Payment for these roles is negotiable.

Casting call ends January 28th.

***For any enquiries, contact: up2212518@myport.ac.uk***

***I've included the link to the*** ***casting call below.***

items.text:
Filmmakers!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions. 

This is more than just filmmaking; it's a journey to elevate our craft and careers to new heights! Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free! 

Complete this form to join us. https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7

items.text:
CASTING CALL for a 10-minute short FILM !!
We are looking for actors for our short film!

Please send your headshot, resume, and demo reel to jooheekim.film@gmail.com

Project name: After The Rain
Director: Joohee Kim
Shoot Dates: Feb 2026

This film explores staying vs. leaving, language barriers, and emotional distance through an intimate, dialogue-driven structure.
Most scenes are two-handers, focusing on subtle emotional shifts rather than dramatic action.

NOTES
* Low-budget / passion project
* Meals & screen credit provided
* Ideal for actors interested in voiceover, minimalist acting, and arthouse storytelling

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‚ÄòNight Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races and ethnicities are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA ‚ÄúMAMA‚Äù CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie‚Äôs calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

items.text:
Hello everyone,
We are a young French filmmaking team currently developing an ambitious project that will be shot across three countries: France, England and Morocco (planned for spring/summer 2026).
This is a very personal, carefully written story with a strong festival ambition (Clermont-Ferrand, C√¥t√© Court, Premiers Plans, international festivals, etc.).
Visually driven, intimate, cinematic atmosphere.
We are looking for:
Actors and actresses aged 18‚Äì25 (very open regarding look, style, background)
All profiles welcome: complete beginners with strong motivation, drama school students, emerging actors, faces already seen in shorts, etc.
Important info:
‚Ä¢  Unpaid project (very low/no budget ‚Äì young indie cinema)
‚Ä¢  But real opportunity: meaningful role(s), several weeks of shooting, travel (France/UK/Morocco), serious festival run potential, nice team, high-quality visuals
How to apply (mandatory elements):
Send an email to:
rivierebouchaud@gmail.com
Required in your email:
‚Ä¢  Recent photos (portrait + at least one medium/full-body shot if possible)
‚Ä¢  A few words about yourself / your background / why this project interests you
(Optional but appreciated: showreel link / theatre recording / self-tape)
Please put in the subject line:
CASTING ‚Äì [Your first name] ‚Äì [your city/country]
We recommend sending your application within the next 3 weeks so we can move forward smoothly with selections.
Thank you so much for your time and energy!
We‚Äôre really excited to discover new faces to bring this international adventure to life.
Looking forward to reading you

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì AMBER (LEAD ROLE)**

**Short Film | Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller**

Hello everyone,

We‚Äôre reopening casting for the **lead role of Amber** due to an unexpected last-minute change. The actress previously cast had to step away for a paid commitment. There are no hard feelings ‚Äî we completely understand and wish her the best. This does, however, mean we‚Äôre reaching out again in hopes of finding the right person to step in and collaborate with us.
**PROJECT DETAILS**

**Project:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Shoot Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Date:** **Sunday, January 18th**
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project

All preparation is already in place. If you‚Äôre available and able to step in, you would genuinely be **saving the day** and helping us keep the shoot on track.
**ROLE: AMBER**

**Age Range:** 27‚Äì40
**Gender:** Female
**Ethnicity:** Open / Race-agnostic
**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chase‚Äîalways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she begins to rely on it too heavily. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern life‚Äînot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.
**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a **subtle, internal performance**. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amber‚Äôs collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettling‚Äîdriven by over-certainty and a loss of trust in her own judgment.
**KEY TRAITS**
* Intelligent
* Controlled
* Ambitious (not arrogant)
* Emotionally guarded
* Increasingly detached
**AUDITION / SUBMISSION**

Self-tape audition
One dramatic scene (sides will be provided)

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (if available)

**Email:** soultales.ca@gmail.com
**Subject:** AMBER ‚Äì Casting Submission

DEXX es cocina de alto riesgo: no para llenar el est√≥mago, sino para transformar el cuerpo.

Empieza donde empieza todo lo serio: investigaci√≥n.

Antes del fuego est√°n los alimentos. 

Su origen. 

Su cuidado. 

El respeto. 

En DEXX, esos ‚Äúalimentos‚Äù son tu t√©cnica, tu historia, tu fatiga, tu rabia, tu silencio, tu disciplina. 

No se improvisa con materia viva. 

Se escucha.

Luego llega el proceso. 

El corte. 

La reducci√≥n. 

La espera. 

La paciencia que parece lenta, pero en realidad est√° afinando el sabor. 

Y aqu√≠ aparece la met√°fora real: DEXX es una olla a presi√≥n. 

No para correr sin sentido, sino para acelerar con fundamento.

La olla a presi√≥n tiene una ley: si no hay base, revienta. Por eso DEXX no empieza por el ‚Äúestilo‚Äù, empieza por el suelo: el principio. 

La estructura. 

El porqu√© del movimiento. 

El cuerpo entendido como laboratorio. 

Desde ah√≠, con respeto y m√©todo, la presi√≥n se convierte en potencia: el aprendizaje se vuelve exponencial, la creatividad deja de ser inspiraci√≥n caprichosa y se vuelve sistema.

Y el resultado no es ‚Äúun plato m√°s‚Äù. 

Es un plato elaborado, raro, valiente, con valor a√±adido:
m√°s profundidad, m√°s conciencia, m√°s filo.

En plena revoluci√≥n de la IA, donde las m√°quinas ejecutan tareas humanas con velocidad pero sin alma, DEXX decide algo inc√≥modo: no competir en rapidez superficial. 

Competir en lo √∫nico que la IA no puede copiar del todo: conciencia real.

La IA puede producir. 

Puede combinar. 

Puede acelerar.

Pero no puede habitar el temblor exacto de una decisi√≥n humana.

No puede entender el precio de una cicatriz en el cuerpo.

No puede convertir experiencia en verdad.

Por eso DEXX es ‚Äúdanza como IA‚Äù solo en una cosa: crecimiento constante, minuto a minuto. 

Pero con una diferencia crucial: lo hace con creatividad y presencia. 

Es decir, no te vuelves m√°quina. 

Te vuelves m√°s humano.

DEXX es darle la vuelta a la tortilla:

si la era exponencial quiere reducirnos a ejecutores, DEXX te entrena para ser creador.

Si el futuro se acelera, DEXX te ense√±a a acelerar sin perderte.

M√°s grande cada minuto, s√≠.

Pero tambi√©n m√°s consciente.

M√°s creativo.

M√°s humano que nunca, dentro del arte.
